The paper discusses a probabilistic approach to item response theory (IRT) using a sparsity-promoting horseshoe prior and a Bayesian neural network. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of the widely applicable information criterion (WAIC) for dimensionality selection, which falls under statistics (cs.ST). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of IRT models in various domains, such as education and psychology, which falls under social and information sciences (cs.SI) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
